    <text id="F0939T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>W. Maxwell offers Cameron his services in promoting his candidacy for
                senator.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>
        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Simon Cameron</name>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1862-12-16">Dec 16<hi rend="super">th</hi> 1862</date>
                        <name type="place">Mercer Pa</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Genl S. Cameron<lb/> Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>My son wrote me that he had seen you in <abbr expan="Philadelphia">Phila</abbr> -
                    He wished me to have our members vote for you for U. S. Senator.</p>

                <p>If you wish for the vote of our Members, I have some influence with them and I
                    think I can induce one at least of them to.</p>

                <p>My work of life has been never to forget a friend and always to be at the service
                    of my friends, if you wish my services - please say so &amp; I will go to
                    work -</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours truly</salute>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="underline">W. Maxwell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
